# Commit messages

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/). One logical change per commit when possible.

## Subject line (required)

- Pattern: `type(optional-scope): imperative description`
- **Types**: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `chore`, `ci`, `build`
- **Scopes** (use when helpful): `web`, `sync`, `ci`, `deps`, `content`
- Imperative mood (“add”, “fix”, not “added”, “fixes”)
- Lowercase after the colon; no trailing period; aim for ~50 characters (hard cap ~72)
- **Breaking changes**: add `!` after type/scope, e.g. `feat(api)!: remove legacy endpoint`, or document in body/footer

## Body (optional)

- Blank line after subject; explain **why** and non-obvious **what**; wrap at ~72 characters
- Reference issues: `Fixes #123` or `Refs #123` in footer when relevant

## Examples

```
feat(articles): add slug-based article page

fix(sync): retry transient network errors on fetch

chore(deps): bump next to 16.2.1

ci: add lint-staged and husky pre-commit
```

## Do not

- Vague subjects (“update”, “fixes”, “wip”)
- Mix unrelated changes in one commit without a clear umbrella scope and body
